def: Furnished with a leaflike appendage, as the fruit of the elmand the ash, or the stem in certain plants; alate.
A South American stork (Euxenara maguari), having a forkedtail.
The act of excusing; seizure by law. [Obs.] Ayliffe.
A genus of plants including all true grapevines.
Lacking substance, as a tenuous argument.
A tool with a cutting edge on one end of a metal blade, used indressing, shaping, or working in timber, stone, metal, etc.; --usually driven by a mallet or hammer. Cold chisel. See under Cold, a.
The act of darkening, or state of being dark; darkness;obscurity. Johnson.
Liable to, or deserving, vituperation, or severe censure.
The quality of being amicable; friendliness; amicableness. Ash.
Of or pertaining to herbs. Quarles.
